contemplation:
To contemplate the miraculous healing of the young man whom the devil tormented, at times throwing him into the fire and at times into the water:

Lord, have pity on my son: for he is a lunatic and suffers severely; for often times he falls into the fire and often times into the water (St. Matthew 17:14):

1. How the Lord rebuked the devil, and the young man was made whole;

2. How the evil spirit also casts me at times into the fire of passions and at times into the water of carnality;

3. How the Lord can also save me from falling into the fire and into the water, if only I pray to Him.
